<div id="node-912" class="node">


  <h2><a href="/blog/maker-fair-nyc-fabricit" title="Maker Fair NYC: Fabric.it">Maker Fair NYC: Fabric.it</a></h2>

  <div class="content clear-block">
    <p>Despina Papadopoulos and Zach Eveland at Maker Faire NYC showed off <a href="http://www.fabrick.it/">Fabrick.it</a>, a set of sewable and snapable electronic modules for creating interactive fashions and wearable prototypes. The fabrick.it collection includes a removable, rechargeable Coin Cell Battery Brick, x-LED Brick with built-in resistor, and a Snap Connector Brick which makes connections fast and easy. The modules are connected with a washable and sewable 3-wire conductive fabric ribbon. </p>
<p><iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/15665269?portrait=0" frameborder="0" height="256" width="455"></iframe></p>
<a href="/blog/maker-fair-nyc-fabricit" >Continue Reading &raquo;</a>  </div>
  
    
